OL,5,Cfrontline
OL,7,FA 27-year-old man from East Yorkshire
OL,8,Fwho joined the Ukrainian army as a
OL,9,Fvolunteer has had his left foot
OL,10,Famputated after stepping on a landmine.
OL,12,FTom, whose surname has been omitted
OL,13,Ffor security reasons, was transported
OL,14,Ffrom the frontline in the Donbas
OL,15,Fregion to hospital in Lviv, where he
OL,16,Fis recovering from his injury.
OL,18,FHe told ITV Calendar that he was
OL,19,Fwalking with teammates through
OL,20,Fwoodland and was looking overhead for
OL,21,Fdrones when he heard an explosion.
