OL,3,CBritish volunteer who lost foot in
OL,4,CUkraine 'determined' to go back to
OL,5,Cfrontline
OL,7,FHe said: "Before I could think or do
OL,8,Fanything, I had already fallen to the
OL,9,Fground on my back. Weirdly, the very
OL,10,Ffirst second, I thought that it was my
OL,11,Fteammate who had been injured.
OL,13,F"It was a bit of an out of body
OL,14,Fexperience... Then I realised it was
OL,15,Fme that had been injured."
OL,17,FTom said it was adrenaline in the
OL,18,Fmoment that enabled him to stick to
OL,19,Fhis training.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/9
