OL,7,FHe said he started to realise the
OL,8,Fextent of his injury when he began
OL,9,Fwrapping a tourniquet around his leg.
OL,11,F"By that point I was able to start
OL,12,Fthinking. My hearing came back a
OL,13,Flittle bit and I realised that I had
OL,14,Fstepped on a mine.
OL,16,F"I could see my foot was badly
OL,17,Fdamaged, sort of limp. I'd broken my
OL,18,Fankle from the blast."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/9
