OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F362A1757854698
OL,3,CBritish volunteer who lost foot in
OL,4,CUkraine 'determined' to go back to
OL,5,Cfrontline
OL,7,F"If you see an injustice in the world
OL,8,Fyou want to go and do something to
OL,9,Fhelp if you're able to help. I'm young
OL,10,Fenough and fit enough to be able to
OL,11,Fhelp, especially as a soldier.
OL,13,F"It's something I thought I would be
OL,14,Fgood at and I was good at it until I
OL,15,Fstepped on this mine."
OL,17,FAfter being taken to hospital in Lviv,
OL,18,FTom had to choose whether to have his
OL,19,Ffoot amputated or rebuilt.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G6/9
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
