OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F362A1757854698
OL,3,CBritish volunteer who lost foot in
OL,4,CUkraine 'determined' to go back to
OL,5,Cfrontline
OL,7,F"The most difficult part is not being
OL,8,Fable to just stand up and walk
OL,9,Fnormally, I'm using crutches at the
OL,10,Fmoment.
OL,12,F"But a lot of people (in hospital)
OL,13,Fhave far more extensive amputations
OL,14,Fthan I have. Triple amputees,
OL,15,Famputations above the knee. I really
OL,16,Fdon't think I can complain too much."
OL,18,FTom said he is expecting to be in
OL,19,Fhospital recovering for a few months
OL,20,Fbut wants to return to his unit once
OL,21,Fhe has his prosthetic foot.
